defaultI think these recommendations would help give your report a broader national perspective on the issue of cycle safety outside major cities.  
defaultThat is not to say that the issues emerging from the London debate (HGV safety, segregation, cycle training and redesign of junctions)
default are not also relevant in rural and suburban areas.  We would just like a tiny fraction of the attention (and the generous
default funding) which is being directed towards cycle safety in London to be channelled in our direction as well.
